17/17 + 17/16 + 17/15 + 17/14 + 17/13 + ... + 17/1 = 58.5 ethereal parchments.<br>
<br>
Wizards need:<br>
8/8 + 8/7 + 8/6 + 8/5 + 8/4 + 8/3 + 8/2 + 8/1 = 21.7 ethereal parchments.<br>
<br>
Now you may say, &quot;oh so what.  We get more spells, and more spells is a good thing.&quot; While I would agree with you there, the more parchments we get, the harder it becomes for us to get another one that we actually need instead of a duplicate.  If both a mage and a wizard have one spell left that they need, a wizard will need on average, 8 ethereal parchments to get that spell.  A magician would need 17.  That is a lot of duplicates!  It kind of irks me that meleers can be exping in areas that yield them the best exp, while we have to be in certain spots, killing certain things for spells, thereby sacrificing the possible good experience.  The only consolation is that magicians can trade spells with each other to complete their collections.<br>
<br>
I believe that SoE should have put all these spells for sale on merchants, and gave everyone an equal amount of spells that were upgrades to the ones on these merchants by implementing the parchment system on boss mobs only.  In other words, only bosses would drop parchments, and the parchments would yield &quot;Ancient&quot; spells instead of the normal ones that everyone needs in order to scale with levels. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.lehigh.edu/~dsf3/EQ/rhionsligo.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <br>
